<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_72047efb-d916-4db4-a300-2fed6d1162f3" outputclass="ncc-clause"><sptc>B6F1</sptc><title id="_3e5efa09-3b2c-4c78-b585-1d422d06e7d3">Rainwater service</title><archive-num>2019: BF6</archive-num><subclause id="_11252279-083c-49a9-871e-3aea01eb8a24" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_5ef9bdf9-7c14-4ded-9a1b-a771dbaa2389">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>A <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1422_4.4.0.xml#_bd764954-3054-4109-81f2-164feefc5058" id="_b5eaa557-86ff-4c58-a4ed-81ce3548b3ec" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">rainwater service</xref> must be designed and installed so as to operate in a way that avoids the likelihood of inadvertent contamination of any <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1250_0.7.0.xml#_762d6a54-e28c-400b-b9c5-5fceac019a05" id="_98e47f14-7d20-423f-a0a8-c785aa16d87b" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">drinking water</xref> service and minimises any adverse impact on building occupants, the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1376_4.2.0.xml#_12d6153c-4986-4856-80c0-e21bb57af12f" id="_fcab32ca-5c8d-4c3d-a722-062619cc7f1a" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">Network Utility Operator’s</xref> infrastructure, property and the environment.</p></subclause></clause>